title: A Maximum Rank Theorem for Solutions to the Homogenous Complex Monge-Ampère Equation in a $\mathbb{C}$-Convex Ring
abstract: Suppose $Ω_0,Ω_1$ are two bounded strongly $\mathbb{C}$-convex domains in $\mathbb{C}^n$, with $n\geq 2$ and $Ω_1\supset\overline{Ω_0}$. Let $\mathcal{R}=Ω_1\backslash\overline{Ω_0}$. We call $\mathcal{R}$ a $\mathbb{C}$-convex ring. We will show that for a solution $Φ$ to the homogenous complex Monge-Ampère equation in $\mathcal{R}$, with $Φ=1$ on $\partialΩ_1$ and $Φ=0$ on $\partialΩ_0$, $\sqrt{-1}\partial\overline{\partial}Φ$ has rank $n-1$ and the level sets of $Φ$ are strongly $\mathbb{C}$-convex.
